        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Along the lines of PDO::MYSQL_ATTR_INIT_COMMAND, I'd like to see a unified option to specify a query \/ command or set of commands to execute upon connection of a Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract instance.\r\n\r\nI think this would be reasonably easy to implement as a hook into the abstract _connect() method.\r\n\r\nMy use case is for setting the NLS_DATE_FORMAT in Oracle connections. At the moment, I'm setting this as soon as the adapter is initialised, thus forcing a connection even if not required, eliminating any lazy loading goodness.\r\n\r\nThere are of course other applications for such a feature, the above is just an example of where I'd use it."
        },
